Program: Discovery
Title: The fish with fingers
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx1v
Last Broadcast Date: 15 January 1998
New evolutionary theories on finger and toe development. The discovery of a fossilised fish which has both a fin and toes with bones suggests the evolution of fingers and toes might not be as cut and dried as had been thought. Also in the programme vaccines for Ebola and house dust mites. Presenter: Graham Easton. Show less